fix(authors): three post-PR2 multi-author bugs

(a) MudAuthorPicker added a chip per keystroke. With CoerceValue="true", MudAutocomplete fires ValueChanged on every typed character — every keystroke became a "committed value" and got added as a new chip. Switch to CoerceValue="false" so ValueChanged only fires when the user picks from the dropdown; add an OnKeyDown handler that reads the displayed text via the component ref and commits on Enter or comma. This preserves the autocomplete dropdown for existing-Author suggestions while only adding a chip when the user actually intends one.

(b) Bulk Add Author placeholder rendered "—" as literal text instead of an em dash. The Razor file stored the escape sequence as text rather than the codepoint — replaced with the actual em dash character. Same fix on the row.Title null-fallback strings (which were already correct as C# string literals; they now use the literal character for consistency).

(c) Open Library lookups timing out 2-3 of 5 in real bulk-scan use. Bumped HttpClient timeout from 10s to 25s — gives the upstream APIs more headroom while still capping the worst case so a hung connection doesn't block the UI indefinitely.

322 tests pass.

